<%- include("partials/header", { pageTitle: "About" }) %>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/general/about.css">
</head>
    <body class="about-body">
        <%- include('partials/navbar') %>
        <main class="about-page">
            <section class="field-hero">
                <div class="field-hero-inner">
                    <span class="field-tag">EST. 2016 — COASTAL FIELD STATION, MAINE</span>
                    <h1>A logbook<br><span>of quiet places.</span></h1>
                    <p class="field-hero-sub">
                        Forty-one stays, each one found on foot,
                        slept in by someone on our team,
                        and entered into the record.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="entry-section">
                <div class="entry-grid">
                    <div class="entry-meta">
                        <span class="entry-date">MARCH, 2016</span>
                        <span class="entry-coords">44.09° N, 69.86° W</span>
                        <span class="entry-line"></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="entry-body">
                        <span class="field-tag">HOW IT STARTED</span>
                        <h2>Shubhayan was counting birds,<br>not building a company.</h2>
                        <p>
                            Shubhayan spent six winters tracking eider ducks
                            along the Maine coast, logging every cove where
                            they wintered undisturbed. The work meant staying
                            close to the water, so she converted the loft
                            above her boat shed into a single room and let it
                            to the handful of researchers passing through.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Word moved slower than the birds did. A hiker
                            asked to stay a night. Then a couple driving the
                            coast road. By the second winter the loft was
                            booked further out than her fieldwork schedule,
                            and she'd started keeping two logs instead of
                            one — nesting sites in the front of the
                            notebook, guests in the back.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="entry-photo">
                        <img src="/images/about-story.png">
                        <span class="photo-caption">Fig. 1 — The boat shed loft, the week it was first listed.</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="notebook-section">
                <div class="notebook-page">
                    <span class="field-tag">FIELD NOTE, NO. 04</span>
                    <p class="notebook-quote">
                        A place doesn't need saving from its guests.
                        It needs guests who don't need saving from quiet.
                    </p>
                    <span class="notebook-attrib">— from Shubhayan's original guest ledger, 1997</span>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="log-section">
                <div class="log-top">
                    <span class="field-tag">THE LOG</span>
                    <h2>How one loft<br>became forty-one.</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="log-list">

                    <div class="log-entry">
                        <span class="log-year">2016</span>
                        <div class="log-thumb"><img src="/images/moment4.png"></div>
                        <div class="log-content">
                            <h3>The Field Station</h3>
                            <p>One room above a boat shed. Booked mostly by ornithologists and one very persistent hiker.</p>
                        </div>
                        <span class="log-count">01</span>
                    </div>

                    <div class="log-entry">
                        <span class="log-year">2018</span>
                        <div class="log-thumb"><img src="/images/moment1.jpg"></div>
                        <div class="log-content">
                            <h3>The Lighthouse Keeper's House</h3>
                            <p>A decommissioned keeper's cottage on Isle au Haut, restored plank by plank over two winters.</p>
                        </div>
                        <span class="log-count">02</span>
                    </div>

                    <div class="log-entry">
                        <span class="log-year">2021</span>
                        <div class="log-thumb"><img src="/images/moment2.jpg"></div>
                        <div class="log-content">
                            <h3>The Fire Lookout</h3>
                            <p>A retired forest-service tower in the Cascades, reachable only by a four-mile trail.</p>
                        </div>
                        <span class="log-count">03</span>
                    </div>

                    <div class="log-entry">
                        <span class="log-year">2024</span>
                        <div class="log-thumb"><img src="/images/moment3.png"></div>
                        <div class="log-content">
                            <h3>Forty-one, and counting</h3>
                            <p>Every property still visited in person before it's added to the log. No listings sight-unseen.</p>
                        </div>
                        <span class="log-count">04</span>
                    </div>

                    <div class="log-entry">
                        <span class="log-year">2026</span>
                        <div class="log-thumb">
                            <img src="/images/moment5.jpg" alt="Verified homes">
                        </div>
                        <div class="log-content">
                            <h3>A Growing Collection</h3>
                            <p>Over one hundred hand-verified stays now fill the log, each chosen for its character, thoughtful hosts, and the kind of quiet that's increasingly difficult to find.</p>
                        </div>
                        <span class="log-count">05</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="criteria-section">
                <div class="criteria-grid">
                    <div class="criteria-photo">
                        <img src="/images/about-world.png">
                    </div>
                    <div class="criteria-copy">
                        <span class="field-tag">HOW WE CHOOSE</span>
                        <h2>Not every quiet place<br>makes the log.</h2>
                        <ul class="criteria-list">
                            <li><span class="criteria-mark">✓</span> Visited and slept in by someone on our team before it's listed</li>
                            <li><span class="criteria-mark">✓</span> At least a mile, or a mountain, from the nearest highway noise</li>
                            <li><span class="criteria-mark">✓</span> One host, reachable by phone, who actually lives nearby</li>
                            <li><span class="criteria-mark">✓</span> Nothing added or changed without the original owner's blessing</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="promise-section">
                <div class="promise-grid">
                    <div class="promise-card">
                        <span class="promise-card-label">NOTE 01 — WHAT WE BELIEVE</span>
                        <p>
                            A well-kept place doesn't announce itself.
                            It just works — the woodstove draws, the water
                            runs hot, the door locks the first try.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="promise-card">
                        <span class="promise-card-label">NOTE 02 — OUR WORD</span>
                        <p>
                            If a stay doesn't match its log entry — the
                            quiet, the host, any of it — tell us within a
                            day. We'll rebook you or refund it. No forms.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="stamp-block">
                    <div class="stamp">VERIFIED</div>
                    <h2>We'd rather strike a place<br>from the log than let it slide.</h2>
                    <p>
                        We don't manage these places from a spreadsheet.
                        Someone drives out, checks in on the host, and
                        re-verifies the listing every season.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <div class="vertical-divider"></div>
            <section class="closing-section">
                <div class="closing-inner">
                    <span class="field-tag light">ENTRY NO. 42 — OPEN</span>
                    <h2>The boat shed loft<br>is still there, second room and all.</h2>
                    <p>Forty of its siblings are logged and waiting.<br>Go see what an unhurried week does to you.</p>
                    <a href="/homeList" class="closing-cta">Explore the Log →</a>
                </div>
            </section>

        </main>
        <%- include('partials/footer') %>
    </body>
</html>